active.name: Physically Active
active.description: SHOW asks a series of questions about moderate and vigorous activities. The activities are scored and aggregated into units of metabolic equivalent task (MET) minutes. One MET minute is equivalent to the energy burned while seated for one minute. Physically active is defined as at least 600 MET minutes per week.

asthma.name: Diagnosed with Asthma
asthma.description: Percent of people that responded yes to "Has a doctor or other health professional ever told you that you have asthma?"

ate_less.name: Ate Less to Lose Weight
ate_less.description: Among people that reported trying to loose weight within the last year, eating less food is the most popular strategy.

bp_check.name: Blood Pressure Checked
bp_check.description: Percent of people reporting they had their blood pressure checked within the last year.

caregiving.name: Currently Providing Care
caregiving.description: Provided regular, unpaid care for family or friend at least once in the past 12 months. Includes only care activities that are necessary because of illness or disability of the recipient.

cognitive_function.name: Cognitive Function
cognitive_function.description: The Mini-Cog is a 3-minute instrument to screen for cognitive impairment. Subjects are told three words, asked to draw a clock diagram, and then asked to recall the words.

count_walk_to.name: Average Number of Amenities
count_walk_to.description: SHOW asks respondents to rate a list of 18 amenities (e.g. parks, supermarkets, post office) on the amount of time it would take to walk to it. This is a count of the number of amenities that the respondents said they could walk to in under 5 minutes.

current_smoker.name: Current Smokers
current_smoker.description: Percent of people that answered yes to the question, "Do you smoke cigarettes now?"

depression.name: Depression Symptoms
depression.description: Depression symptoms as defined by the DSM-IV. The diagnostic criteria for depression is at least 5 symptoms present in the past 30 days and some report of either depressed mood or anhedonia (little interest or pleasure in doing things).

designated_driver.name: Use Designated Driver
designated_driver.description: People that report always using a designated driver or that the question does not apply (they do not drink or they do not drive).

diabetes.name: Diabetes
diabetes.description: A doctor has told you that you have type 1 or type 2 diabetes. (Excludes gestational diabetes and pre-diabetes.)

discrimination.name: Experienced Discrimination
discrimination.description: SHOW asks if participants have felt unfairly treated at any time over their live in a number of settings (e.g. school, work, housing). This is the percent of people that have reported discrimination at least once in their life.

dozing_off.name: High Chance of Dozing Off
dozing_off.description: SHOW asks if people would be likely to doze off while doing one of 8 activities (e.g. watching TV, riding in a car). This is the percent of people that reported a high chance of dozing off in at least one situation.

ever_daily_binge_drinker.name: Daily Binge Drinking
ever_daily_binge_drinker.description: Percent of people that report at least one time in their life where they drank 5 or more drinks almost every day.

family_history_cancer.name: Family History of Cancer
family_history_cancer.description: Any blood relatives have been diagnosed with cancer.

flu_shot.name: Annual Flu Vaccine
flu_shot.description: Percent of people that reported they had a flu shot in the last 12 months.

food_insecure.name: Food Insecurity
food_insecure.description: SHOW asks a series of questions about the household's food security. This is the percentage that reported at least one issue with food security within the past year.

fruit_veg_access.name: Access to Fruits and Veggies
fruit_veg_access.description: Percent of people that agree or strongly agree with the statement, "I have easy access to fruits and vegetables in my community."

fruit_veg_eating.name: Average Fruits and Veggies Per Day
fruit_veg_eating.description: SHOW asks respondents for various information about their normal eating habits. Based on their answers an average number of fruits and veggies per day is computed based on standard methods.

gestational_diabetes.name: Diabetes (Gestational)
gestational_diabetes.description: Among women that have had at least one pregnancy, have they ever been told by a doctor that they had gestational diabetes.

heavy_drinker.name: Heavy Drinkers
heavy_drinker.description: Respondents are asked how much wine, beer, and liquor they drink in a normal week. Heavy drinkers are defined by the CDC as men that have more than 15 drinks per week and women that have more than 8 drinks per week.

hiv_testing.name: HIV Tested
hiv_testing.description: Tested for HIV within the last 12 months. (Excluding tests as part of blood donation.)

hypertension.name: Hypertension
hypertension.description: SHOW measures blood pressure for all respondents. People are considered hypertensive if they have BP over 140/90. If a respondent reports they are currently being treated with anti-hypertensive medication they are also considered to have hypertension.

indoor_pesticide.name: Indoor Pesticide Use
indoor_pesticide.description: Using pesticides in at least one room in your home. (Excludes people that responded that they did not know.)

indoor_smoke.name: Exposed to Smoke in their Homes
indoor_smoke.description: Percent of people that report that they or someone they live with smokes in their home.

insurance.name: Insured
insurance.description: SHOW asks multiple questions about health, dental, and prescription drug coverage. This is the percent of people that report having health insurance coverage for all 12 months of the previous year.

internet.name: Used Internet for Health Info
internet.description: In the last 12 months, have you used the internet to seek information or advice on your health, or that of your family?

life_events.name: Number of Life Changes in Past Year
life_events.description: SHOW asks respondents if they have experienced any of a list of 43 life changes (e.g. divorce, moving, changing jobs, change in eating habits). This is the average count of the life changes in the past year.

lung_function.name: Lung Function
lung_function.description: SHOW subjects blow air through a spirometer to measure their lung function. The forced expiratory volume (FEV1%) is the flow that comes out at the beginning and the forced vital capacity (FVC) is the total lung volume. The ratio between FEV1% and FVC can indicate obstructive lung function. This is the percent ab

neighborhood_safety.name: Neighborhood Safety
neighborhood_safety.description: People answering that their neighborhood is "very safe" from crime. (As opposed to somewhat, not very, or not at all safe.)

overweight.name: Overweight
overweight.description: SHOW measures people's height and weight. From this we calculate their body mass index (BMI). A BMI over 25 is considered overweight.

pack_years.name: Average Pack Years among Smokers
pack_years.description: Calculated for people that have ever smoked. It is equivalent to smoking 1 pack per day for 1 year.

poor_oral_health.name: Poor Oral Health (self-reported)
poor_oral_health.description: If respondents reported the condition of their teeth was "fair" or "poor", they are counted in the percent of people reporting poor oral health.

prescriptions.name: Prescription Medication
prescriptions.description: Taking at least one prescription mediation in the last 30 days.

ptsd.name: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder
ptsd.description: SHOW uses the civilian version of the PTSD Check List based on DSM-IV criteria. This is the percent of people that would be diagnosed with PTSD based on their symptom severity scores.

self_rated_health.name: Good Self-rated Health
self_rated_health.description: People answering good, very good, or excellent, when asked for their general health. (As opposed to "fair" or "poor.")

sleep_hours.name: Average Hours of Sleep
sleep_hours.description: SHOW asks a series of questions about work/school nights and weekend nights for respondents that work. This is the average hours of sleep for all respondents.

stress_z.name: Stress
stress_z.description: SHOW asks many questions about how often people feel stress, anxiety, and depression. This is the percent of people that report more stressful feelings than the national average. (National average based on Manual for the Depression Anxiety Stress Scales [1995].)

total_cholesterol.name: Total Cholesterol
total_cholesterol.description: Each respondent that agrees to a blood test is analyzed for total cholesterol by Marshfield Labs.

usual_health_care.name: Place for Usual Health Care
usual_health_care.description: Percentage of people that report having a usual place for health care. (As opposed to going to an emergency room or having no place of usual care.)

vitamins.name: Daily Vitamin Use
vitamins.description: Percentage of people that use vitamins every day.

walk_score.name: Walk Score™
walk_score.description: The calculated Walk Score™ for the home address of the respondent. More information: https://www.walkscore.com/

water_filter.description: People that report using a water filter at home for drinking water.
